  <!-- Launch -->
  <paragraphs>
    <title><custom ref="launch-titulo"/></title>
    <p>[@@@@@@@@@] Remind students of work they did previously to match a situation with an equation. For example, they matched the equation <m>x + 5 = 20</m> with the situation “After Elena ran <m>5</m> miles on Friday, she had run a total of <m>20</m> miles for the week. How many miles did she run before Friday?” In this activity, they come up with their own situations that can be represented by equations.</p>

    <p>
      Keep students in the same groups. Clarify that for each equation, each partner will come up with a story, and one of those stories is chosen. Give students 5–10 minutes to work with their partner, followed by a whole-class discussion.
    </p>
  </paragraphs>


